example.statement:
Classify each function as one of the types of functions discussed in this section.



		k(t) = t-5+t^2




		\ell(x) = (0.25)^x




		m(y) = \dfrac{1-x}{\sqrt{1-x^2}}




		n(\theta) = \theta^{0.25}




		o(r) = \dfrac{r^3-5r^2 + r^4-1}{r^2 + r+10}

Find the domain of the following functions.



		t(k) = \sqrt{k^2-6}




		y(b) = \sec\lrpar{\dfrac{\pi}{2}b}




		h(x) = \dfrac{x+3}{2\sqrt{5-x}}
